-- GS Caltex Appoints Lee Managing Director for Singapore, Relocates Staff
-- B y   Y e e   K a i   P i n
-- 2010-12-14T02:50:39Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-14/gs-caltex-appoints-y-h-lee-as-managing-director-for-singapore-operations.html
GS Caltex Singapore Pte , a
subsidiary of South Korea’s second-largest oil refiner, named Y.
H. Lee as senior vice-president and managing director effective
Jan. 1, the company said in an e-mailed statement.  Lee, vice-president and head of crude and product supply
and trading in Seoul, will take over from  Saehong Hur  as the
most senior official in Singapore, according to the statement,
dated Dec. 10 and released today. Hur was appointed senior vice-
president and refinery manager of operation planning at GS
Caltex’s Yeosu refinery.  Privately held  GS Caltex  trades Middle East and Asian crude
and products in Singapore, the region’s biggest oil-trading and
storage center. Its Yeosu refinery has a capacity of 770,000
barrels a day, ranking behind SK Energy Co.’s Ulsan plant, based
on data compiled by Bloomberg.  Two other officials will relocate to Seoul, the company
said. Singapore-based head of crude and product trading, C. B.
Lee, will assume Y. H. Lee’s current position and senior
products manager T. Y. Shim will join the light product trading
team in the South Korean capital.  Y. K. Suh, general manager for light products, will move to
Singapore as general manager for the product team, according to
the statement.  GS Caltex, which employs about 20 people in Singapore, also
has a Beijing representative office and an office in London,
according to its  website . South Korea is Asia’s fourth-largest
economy and imports almost all of its oil.  To contact the reporter on this story:
